The current slice is an anemic CRUD update. The smallest correction is to move the issuance rule into the `Invoice` aggregate, replace primitive money/state handling with domain types, and make the application service only coordinate persistence and publication.

A minimal shape would be:

```ts
type InvoiceStatus = "DRAFT" | "ISSUED";

class Money {
  private constructor(
    readonly amountMinor: number,
    readonly currency: string,
  ) {}

  static ofMinor(amountMinor: number, currency: string): Money {
    if (!Number.isInteger(amountMinor)) throw new Error("invalid money");
    return new Money(amountMinor, currency);
  }

  isPositive(): boolean {
    return this.amountMinor > 0;
  }
}

class InvoiceLine {
  constructor(readonly total: Money) {
    if (!total.isPositive()) throw new Error("invalid line");
  }
}

class InvoiceIssued {
  constructor(
    readonly invoiceId: string,
    readonly issuedAt: Date,
  ) {}
}

class Invoice {
  constructor(
    readonly id: string,
    private status: InvoiceStatus,
    private lines: InvoiceLine[],
    private total: Money,
    private dueDate: Date,
    private issuedAt?: Date,
  ) {}

  issue(now: Date): InvoiceIssued {
    if (this.status !== "DRAFT") throw new Error("only draft invoices can be issued");
    if (this.lines.length === 0) throw new Error("invoice must contain at least one valid line");
    if (!this.total.isPositive()) throw new Error("invoice total must be positive");

    this.status = "ISSUED";
    this.issuedAt = now;
    return new InvoiceIssued(this.id, now);
  }
}
```

Repository change: replace `genericRepository` usage with an aggregate-oriented `InvoiceRepository` such as `getById(id)` and `save(invoice)`. It should reconstitute `Invoice`, `InvoiceLine`, and `Money`; it should not return raw rows or enforce issuance rules.

Service change: keep `issueInvoice` as an application service, but make it only coordinate the use case:

```ts
export async function issueInvoice(id: string): Promise<void> {
  await tx.run(async () => {
    const invoice = await invoiceRepository.getById(id);
    if (!invoice) throw new Error("invoice not found");

    const event = invoice.issue(new Date());
    await invoiceRepository.save(invoice);
    await eventPublisher.publish(event);
  });
}
```

That satisfies the rule split:
- `Invoice` enforces `DRAFT` and line/total invariants.
- `Money` owns currency-safe arithmetic instead of `number`.
- issuing records `issuedAt` and produces `InvoiceIssued`.
- the application layer owns transaction and publication coordination.

I would not add a domain service here. Issuing is single-aggregate behavior and fits naturally on `Invoice` itself.
